      <hedline>
        <hl1>Fear of Failure? Back Up</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Steven A Ludsin says May 18 article on making backups did not mention Iomega's Jaz drive for storage and backup</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The article about making backups did not mention Iomega's Jaz drive for storage and backup. Jaz disks are the big brothers of the 100- and 250-megabyte Zip disks. Jaz disks hold 1 or 2 gigabytes of data, which is the total size of the hard drives of many older PCs. There are internal drives available, but I prefer the external drives because they are portable.</p>
        <p>STEVEN A. LUDSIN  East Hampton, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
